<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aleksandar Mitrovic made a scoring return to the starting line-up for Fulham as he secured their progression to the next round of the Carabao Cup. </p>

<p>The powerful forward converted Kenny Tete's cross in the first half at Portman Road. </p>

<p>Scott Parker's side dominated both possession and creation of chances but struggled to find their way through Ipswich. </p>

<p>More to follow...  </p>

<p>Kenny Tete (left) delivered the assist and Aleksandar Mitrovic made no mistake with his head</p>

<p>The powerful forward timed his header to perfection in between the Ipswich defenders</p>

<p>Mitrovic's goal came in the 38th minute and flew past Ipswich goalkeeper David Cornell</p>

<p>The Premier League side dominated the opening period and found their rewards </p>

<p>Fulham will look to continue their momentum into the Premier League having lost to Arsenal</p>
